*audacious-1.1.0_beta2-r1 (15 Jun 2006)

  15 Jun 2006; Michael Hanselmann <hansmi@gentoo.org>
  +files/util-filesize.diff, +audacious-1.1.0_beta2-r1.ebuild:
  Added patch to fix crash with some skin files.

*audacious-1.1.0_beta2 (12 Jun 2006)

  12 Jun 2006; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org>
  +audacious-1.1.0_beta2.ebuild:
  Version bump. Features subsong support for console music (NSF/NSFE/GBS) and
  improved stability.

  06 Jun 2006; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> audacious-1.0.0-r1.ebuild:
  Mark stable on ppc. Approved: hansmi.

  06 Jun 2006; Simon Stelling <blubb@gentoo.org> audacious-1.0.0-r1.ebuild:
  stable on amd64

*audacious-1.1.0_beta1 (20 May 2006)

  20 May 2006; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org>
  +audacious-1.1.0_beta1.ebuild:
  Bump to 1.1.0 developer release 1. The configfile interface has been
  poisoned, nobody should have been using this since the 0.2 versions. Moving
  dialogs should no longer corrupt the screen when composite X is used. Proxy
  settings are unified, and the musepack playback no longer cuts out a few
  seconds too early. The AAC plugin has had an overhaul, be sure to test that.
  Taglib is now used for ID3 tags, which should help with UTF-8 related
  difficulties.

*audacious-1.0.0-r1 (29 Apr 2006)

  29 Apr 2006; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org> +audacious-1.0.0-r1.ebuild:
  Install header files in correct location, closes bug #130964 by Dominik
  Stadler <centic@gentoo.org>. Add timidity USE-flag as requested by Roman
  Polach <rpolach@atlas.cz> in bug #131018. Revision bumped.

  22 Apr 2006; Tony Vroon <chainsaw@gentoo.org>
  -files/0.2-no-sigabrt-on-null-path.diff, -files/0.2-segfault.diff,
  -files/0.2-thumbnail.diff, -audacious-0.1.2.ebuild,
  -audacious-0.2-r1.ebuild, -audacious-0.2.1.ebuild,
  -audacious-0.2.2.ebuild:
  Clean up old ebuilds & patches. (Note that the mips arch had no stable
  ebuild before, so lack of a stable mips keyword does not block this.)

